Mentioned it before, but you should have a small dose of alcohol every day if you're not a drinker. Half a shot of rum, a few tablespoons of vodka in your tea, etc. Alcohol is the only thing that dissolves lipofuscin which causes aging spots, participates in atherosclerosis, etc.

Bigger amounts apparently do not dissolve more lipofuscin, so I guess the important thing is to just take a miniscule amount of alcohol every single day. An ounce of champagne. A single sip of whiskey. You don't have to feel it, but gets you the biggest health benefit of alcohol.
